{
  "stem": "10406.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in August of '44, the Russians were closing in, coming.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, German-- basically, the German front was falling apart.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they were still fighting.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Chelm was already liberated by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But some fanatic German division decided to make a stand in the village where I lived, in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So-- and the Russians saw what was happening.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they let-- they bypassed it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They left it alone.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they kept going.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then they surrounded the village.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And you were liberated then.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And about a week later, they attacked like full attack.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The roofs were flying.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they liberated, you know, the village.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I still have arguments.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, I don't have arguments anymore.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, people that get involved in that, I tell them that it's not really God.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They have a problem.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They have a problem in interpretation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They have a problem in expectation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What do you expect to God?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "God never told anybody that if he's sitting there ready to be shot that he's going to grab the rifle and protect him.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's not-- it's-- For me, it was very sad to see the most righteous of people in Judaism, old men with white beards that were sincere and religious being taken, you know, by these hoodlums to be shot.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And basically, they saying to God, God, you know, certain prayers, [NON-ENGLISH], you know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Or why did you forsake me and, and Shema Yisrael.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I felt-- I mean-- Even after the war, I felt very bad that they went to such a death.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But maybe that was our problem.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Maybe the Jews in that part of the world lived a fantasy life where they were so happy in their religion.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "On [NON-ENGLISH], we came to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it was dancing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And every Saturday night, you know, praying and dancing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was a, a, a happy religious life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And perhaps-- And being, like, concentrated in-- together in towns like a ghetto almost maybe, maybe felt secure.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But obviously, there was no security there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And younger people that wanted to leave for Palestine, for Israel, at that time were-- were not allowed in a lot of cases by their parents.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "A lot of people, especially the younger generation, the Zionists, you know, could have-- a lot of people could have gotten out, although that wasn't easy because the British didn't let you in there, you know, so it was a-- But I have my own thinking and philosophy about religion that people that want to blame God-- don't blame God, because God didn't do it.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Like some religious fanatics, idiots, will come out and say that actually God did this to those Jews over there because they weren't good enough, because the German Jews started assimilating, so therefore, all of them had to pay the price.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I made some-- yeah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some-- one of my aunts comes to Chelm and finds out through that man that brought me there and that gardener that I went for food lived in Chelm.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They also had to run away.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So my aunt met that woman gardener.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and she knew from the other guy that I was in the area.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They didn't know where.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Only that guy knew.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they-- you know, she-- they introduced her.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she and that man came to the farm to take me, you know, back.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so I told my farmer that I'm leaving.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I never told him I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he was crying.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She says-- he says he liked me because I was a good workhorse.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He said good is not for long, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I left.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then we find out that another aunt, who now lives in Connecticut, is in Russia and cannot come back because she doesn't have any papers.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So I decide to make a trip.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I find out what the story was.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I go back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I get her papers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then I end up staying there for less than a year, till, till the war ended, like in May--",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Roughly May of '45.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then I came back, back to, to Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By myself.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But my aunt left earlier.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then I met her there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we went to Germany.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We ended up in the Munich area.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there, I went to one of the ORT schools, learning, like, trades.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then I was able to come to the United States with a group of orphans that it was sponsored-- it was like United-- I don't know if it was a combination, United States and United Nations.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was some group that was sponsoring orphans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I came with that group.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then my grandfather's sister lived here.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I ended up living with her.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
